doctype html
html(lang='en')
  head
    meta(charset='utf-8')
    title The HTML5 Herald
    meta(name='Timestamp Microservice', content='Timepstamp microservice')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='/css/app.css')
    link(href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto:400,500,700|EB+Garamond|Ubuntu+Mono', rel='stylesheet', type='text/css')
    //if lt IE 9
      script(src='http://html5shiv.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js')
  body
    .bodyText
      h1 Timestamp Microserve
      .quote
        h3.subHead User Stories
        ol.offset
          li
            | I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
          li
            | If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
          li
            | If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
      h3
        | Example Usage:
        ul
          li.example
            a https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/December%2015,%202015
          li.example
            a https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/1450137600
        h3
          | Example Output:
          p.example { "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }